🧪 Practical 4
🎯 Title

Transfer files from one virtual machine to another virtual machine

📝 Steps (Write in Journal)
🔹 Step 1: Install VirtualBox
Download and install
👉 Oracle VM VirtualBox
🔹 Step 2: Get Ubuntu Image
Download Ubuntu ISO OR VMDK
👉 Ubuntu
🔹 Step 3: Create Virtual Machines
VM1:
Name: VM1
Type: Linux
Version: Ubuntu (64-bit)
RAM: 2 GB
Attach: Existing VMDK file
VM2:
Repeat same steps
Name: VM2
🔹 Step 4: Configure Network

For BOTH VMs:

Go to Settings → Network
Adapter 1:
Attached to → Bridged Adapter
Select → Wi-Fi / Ethernet
🔹 Step 5: Start Both VMs
Login using:
username: vagrant
password: vagrant
🔹 Step 6: Get IP Address

In both VMs:

ifconfig
🔹 Step 7: Test Connectivity

From VM1:

ping <VM2-IP>

👉 Stop using:

Ctrl + C
🔹 Step 8: Install SSH

In BOTH VMs:

sudo apt update
sudo apt install openssh-server
🔹 Step 9: Create File in VM1
nano file.txt 
Write content
Save: Ctrl + O → Enter
Exit: Ctrl + X
🔹 Step 10: Transfer File (SCP)
scp file.txt vagrant@<VM2-IP>:/home/vagrant/
🔹 Step 11: Verify in VM2
ls
cat file.txt
🎯 Result

The file was successfully transferred from one virtual machine to another using SCP over SSH.
